        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="1">
            <title>service procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid personal injury or death, shift transmission to park or neutral, set parking brake,
                        and block wheels before doing diagnostic or service procedures.
                    </para>
                    <para>To avoid personal injury or death, let hot engine cool and make sure pressure in the cooling
                        system is released before starting modifications.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen coolant system pressure cap.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Measure back 120 mm (approximately 5") on the top deaeration hose at the surge tank
                    (Figure 1).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0790601" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0790601.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="472px"
                         scalefitheight="336px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. EGR Cooler Deaeration Hose Restrictor</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Cut deaeration hose at the 120 mm (approximately 5") from the surge tank.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install hose clamps from the parts kit on the hose on both sides of the cut.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install restrictor. You will notice that the restrictor has a large hole in one end and
                    a smaller hole in the other end, it makes no difference which way the restrictor is installed.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide clamps along the hose so they are positioned over the ends of the restrictor.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten coolant system pressure cap.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check for leaks and insure that the surge tank is at the full level.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
